<HEADLINE>
FT  18 JUN 93 / London Stock Exchange: R-R foreign buying
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By STEVE THOMPSON, JOEL KIBAZO and CHRISTINE BUCKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Aero-engine manufacturer Rolls-Royce continued to attract overseas interest
and edged forward a halfpenny to 150p in an otherwise poor day for the
market. Volume was 3.2m shares.
US investment bank Lehman Brothers is among those institutions which have
moved to satisfy continuing demand from overseas investors, following last
week's company announcement that the foreign share ownership level had
reached the maximum permitted of 29.5 per cent.
Lehman said it has issued 5m call warrants with a maturity date of December
1994 with the specific aim of satisfying European and US demand for
Rolls-Royce.
Goldman Sachs, the US investment bank, was said earlier this week to be
looking to make a similar move. Currently any further direct purchases by
non-UK investors would have to be relinquished or transferred to UK
ownership as soon as the company confirms the purchases, a move dictated by
its articles of association.
