FT  18 JUN 93 / International Company News: John Labatt losses deepen to
CDollars 204m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
JOHN LABATT, the Canadian brewing and consumer products group, posted a loss
of CDollars 204m (USDollars 159.3m) on revenues of CDollars 446m in the
fourth quarter ended April. A year earlier, Labatt posted a loss of CDollars
23m on revenues of CDollars 379m.
The latest loss stems mainly from continuing problems with Labatt's US dairy
business. The loss included a CDollars 173m write-down in the value of this
operation.
For the whole of 1992-93 the loss was CDollars 70m against a profit of
CDollars 101m a year earlier. Revenues were CDollars 2.1bn against CDollars
1.7bn.
Brewing had an operating profit of CDollars 218m for the year, up from
CDollars 178m.
Labatt recently spun off its Canadian dairy products operations and
classified its US dairy business as a discontinued operation while attempts
are made to sell it.
