FT  18 JUN 93 / International Company News: Klockner-Werke sales dip 5.1% in
opening half
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ARIANE GENILLARD
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BONN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
KLOCKNER-WERKE, the German steel and machinery group, reported half-year
group sales falling by 5.1 per cent to DM3.37bn (Dollars 2.03bn), down from
DM3.56bn for the same period the previous years.
Sales in its steel subsidiaries, Klockner Stahl and Klockner Edelstahl, fell
by 12.3 per cent to DM1.08bn for the six months to March 31.
The company, which recently gained approval from creditors to write off
DM1.4bn of its DM2.7bn net debt, refused to comment on the size of its
operational losses. In the steel divisions, analysts estimate losses at more
than DM200m.
Group sales in Germany fell by 9.7 per cent while sales abroad went down by
a modest 0.2 per cent. However, in the machinery divisions sales for the six
months rose by nearly 2 per cent to DM1.035bn.
