<HEADLINE>
FT  18 JUN 93 / UK Company News: Derwent Valley expands with Pounds 10m
purchase
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CATHERINE MILTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
DERWENT VALLEY Holdings, the property company, is expanding its portfolio
with a Pounds 10.3m cash acquisition of 10 freehold properties funded by way
of a net Pounds 16.9m placing and open offer.
The company believed that values had stabilised and that confidence in the
property market had returned. 'Attractive opportunities for property
investment exist,' the directors said.
Derwent has agreed to buy three freehold office buildings at Wrexham,
Wellingborough and Shoreham, and seven freehold retail properties at
Wallington. The principal purchase, for Pounds 5.25m, is a 54,560 sq ft
office building in Wrexham.
The Pounds 16.9m placing and open offer, fully underwritten by Warburg
Securities, is priced at 450p for each of the 3.8m new shares to be issued -
a discount to Wednesday's closing value of 493p. Qualifying shareholders can
apply at the same price on 1-for-2 basis.
Proceeds will be used to finance the acquisitions.
