<HEADLINE>
FT  18 JUN 93 / UK Company News: Safeland advances 45% to Pounds 242,000
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
PRE-TAX profits of Safeland, the property group, advanced by 45 per cent,
from Pounds 167,000 to Pounds 242,000, in the year to March 31.
The outcome was achieved on turnover up by Pounds 5.25m to Pounds 13.8m and
after reduced interest payable of Pounds 652,000 (Pounds 923,000).
A final dividend of 0.44p (0.14p) makes an improved 0.5p (0.28p) total,
payable from earnings per share of 1p (0.6p).
Mr Raymond Lipman, chairman, said there were now signs of greater activity
within the property market, but there was still a degree of uncertainty.
The chairman added that since the year end Safeland had formed a new
subsidiary, Heritage Insurance Services, which would specialise in property
insurance for the group's own portfolio.
