<HEADLINE>
FT  18 JUN 93 / Record number apply to UCCA
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
APPLICATIONS to the Universities Central Council on Admissions are a record
this year. Total applications by the end of May were 9.1 per cent higher
than at the same point last year.
Vocational courses saw the greatest leap with applications for teacher
training up 32.8 per cent and for medicine up 13.7 per cent.
Academic courses were less popular, with a fall of 4.3 per cent in
applications for history degrees.
The council, which does not handle applications for the 'new' universities -
those which converted from polytechnics last year - predicts that all offers
will be honoured but that students who narrowly miss their conditional
offers will find it much harder than usual to find a place at another
university.
