<HEADLINE>
FT  18 JUN 93 / Almost half London 16-19-year-olds not in education or
training
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
ALMOST half of London's 16-to-19-year-olds are not in education or receiving
training from their employers, according to the Local Economy Policy Unit. A
survey showed 43 per cent are students, 39 per cent are employed and 13 per
cent are unemployed.
