<HEADLINE>
FT  17 JUN 93 / Commodities and Agriculture: CIS aluminium shake-out seen
continuing
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID LASCELLES, Resources Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MORE NORMAL conditions are likely to return to the depressed aluminium
market by the end of 1994, Mr Allen Born, the chairman and chief executive
officer of Amax said yesterday.
Amax is in the process of effecting a merger with Cyprus Minerals in the
course of which Amax will spin off its large aluminium arm, Alumax.
Mr Born, speaking in London, said that this year and next would see a
continuing shake-out in the former Soviet Union where excess capacity was
depressing the aluminium markets. He believed that the Russians might close
some of the capacity down, and develop more fabricating operations to absorb
output.
'There is a need for more discipline in these markets,' he said.
Mr Born also said the outlook for copper 'looks good', though only for low
cost producers.
