FT  17 JUN 93 / International Company News: US tobacco trader expands in
Hungary
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NICHOLAS DENTON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BUDAPEST
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
UNIVERSAL Leaf Tobacco, the US tobacco trader and processor, is to take over
Nyidofer, Hungary's dominant supplier of tobacco for cigarette makers.
Universal's offer involves the acquisition of a 76 per cent shareholding, an
immediate capital increase, a subsequent injection and substantial support
for hard-pressed Hungarian tobacco growers.
Total investment including commitments would amount to about Ft2bn (Dollars
22m), Hungary's State Property Agency privatisation authority said
yesterday.
